In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture. Stir in oats. Press into a greased 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack. In a microwave-safe bowl, melt caramels and water. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with chips, nuts and M&M's. Gently press into the caramel mixture. Melt confectionery coating; drizzle over the top. Cut into bars.